Thupeyo Muleya Beitbridge Bureau Preparations for President Mugabe s interface with party youths in Matabeleland South province have gathered momentum, with the zanu-pf leadership already on the ground mobilising resources. zanu-pf Youth league provincial chairperson, Cde Lwazi Moyo, said last week that they had already set up mobilisation teams in all the seven administrative districts.He said the event will be held at Pelandaba Stadium in Gwanda on a date yet to be advised. We have started mobilising the youths to attend the meeting with President Mugabe in their numbers, said Cde Moyo. Prior to the President s visit we will host our national secretary for Youth Affairs Cde Kudzai Chipanga. He will guide us in coming up with a date. Our main thrust is to encourage zanu-pf youths to register in their numbers, especially the new voters, so that we may rally behind Cde Mugabe as our candidate in 2018. We are looking forward to having a frank and fruitful discussion with our icon .nt that we work as a unity so that we can successfully implement our party s economic emancipation programmes. 